The lecture course introduces modern approaches to social innovation - its' theoretical approaches, principles and practical opportunities. Social innovation is an innovative solution to societal challenges that enables stakeholders to interact, learn and experiment, and therefore the co-creative outcome is more effective and sustainable than the alternatives used so far. The value created by socially innovative solutions is related to society rather than the individual.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide knowledge about social innovation, essence of co-production and responsible governance.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students completing the course will: - Understand the role of innovation in knowledge-based society. - Know challenges of open and inclusive governance. - Be able to evaluate and analyze social innovation initiatives and their societal impact. - Have knowledge of co-production and implementing innovative ideas. - Have an overview of modern professional literature.
